Computer Language: (("Determine language from source") (#(#t print mixed-fraction-e #f #t debug) (default) #() "#lang racket\n" #t #t ((test) (main)) #t))
>Description:
Hi, 

The 'blue box'(1) in doesn't reliably select the identifier at the insertion point.

pressing f2 seems to do double duty as locking the documentation open and selecting a new identifier.

(1) I think 'bluebox' is the name for the pop-down documentation that for the current selected identifier. The DrRacket manual doesn't really cover this functionality AFAICT.
>How-To-Repeat:
1. ensure background check syntax is enabled.
2. place the insertion point in a identifier
3. click [check syntax] 
4. check top-right popup is showing identifier documentation summary 
5. click another identifier
6. check top-right popup - is NOT showing documentation summary for newly selected identifier.
>Fix:
>Audit-Trail:
From: Robby Findler <robby@eecs.northwestern.edu>
To: Stephen De Gabrielle <spdegabrielle@gmail.com>,
        bugs <bugs@racket-lang.org>
Cc: nobody <nobody@racket-lang.org>,
        bug-notification <bug-notification@racket-lang.org>
Subject: Re: [racket-bug] all/15393: 'blue box' in doesn't reliably select the
 identifier at the insertion point
Date: Thu, 5 Jan 2017 09:48:34 -0600

 I think that probably the right fix for this is to change the way the
 check syntax button works so that greys itself out, but others does
 nothing and waits for online expansion to finish.
 
 Does that seem okay to you?
 
 Robby
 
 
