Subject: Re: [racket-bug] all/15393: 'blue box' in doesn't reliably select the
 identifier at the insertion point
Date: Thu, 5 Jan 2017 12:52:27 -0600

 Ah: we're getting into embarrasing details of the current implementation now. :)
 
 When you press the check syntax button, then DrRacket expands and
 grovels over the expanded program, collecting information about where
 arrows should go and things like that. Also, separately (altho reusing
 much of the code (but not all)) when a certain (short) timeout has
 expired, DrRacket does that same process (but in a different `place`).
 Once that process has completed, this information is made available to
 you in a variety of ways, one of those ways is when you press f2 (or
 when you move your mouse around or right click on various things).
 
 So f2 isn't really running the process of checking syntax (which is
 also a historical and thus terrible name), it's looking at the result
 of doing that process. And that's probably the root of the bug: the
 two slightly different versions of the process are probably not doing
 quite the right thing to cause the error you wrote about in the
 initial PR.
 
 Robby
 
 
 
