 On Thu, Jan 5, 2017 at 5:55 PM, Stephen De Gabrielle
 <spdegabrielle@gmail.com> wrote:
 > Thank you for the insight. Am I right in guessing check syntax will be
 > retired in favour of the integrated DrRacket code? or are the two passes
 > required - like a compiler?
 
 I'm not sure. But in general, to run Racket code, it must be compiled
 (and one of those steps is expansion); for DrRacket to annotate your
 code with the arrows and the documentation links, only the expansion
 step needs to be done, so that's all it does in that case.
 
 Mostly I just need to clean up this particular interaction to avoid the bug.
 
 But as advice to you, I would just say to not bother clicking that
 button any more and instead wait for the green dot to appear in the
 bottom right corner of the DrRacket window.
 
 > As for the name - why not change it if you don't like it?
 
 It has been around so long, I guess. I mostly don't think it needs a
 name; it should just be part of the background functionality of
 editing code in DrRacket, ideally.
 
 Robby
